author: Sam Spencer
text:
Now for my #Bundesliga club. If #FCUnion win out, that puts them at 59 points. Then they need a miracle to make #UEFA Champions play.

Their dream scenario:
Leverkusen loses to Freiburg and finishes 1-2-0
OR Leipzig finishes 1-1-1
AND Freiburg finishes no better than 2-1-0/1-0-2

author: Sam Spencer
text: 5th place Freiberg doesn’t quite control its own destiny and may care more about its @DFB_Pokal final at this point. However, if they win out, they will - at the very least - tie Leverkusen in points. #Bundesliga

author: Sam Spencer
text: Even with today’s loss to Union, #RBLeipzig also controls their own destiny as well. Their last two opponents have not escaped relegation so if Augsburg or Arminia decide to fight for their lives, Leipzig could miss Champions League play. #Bundesliga

author: Sam Spencer
text: 3-7 is where it gets interesting in the sprint for international play. Leverkusen is in 3rd but they arguably have the toughest schedule ahead of them with 9th Place Frankfurt, Hoffenheim in 8th, and Freiburg in 5th. They still control their own destiny. #Bundesliga

author: Sam Spencer
text: The loser of today’s #FCBBVB match currently holds second place on the 1. #Bundesliga table. @BVB has an easy schedule for the rest of the season and only needs 2 points to be out of reach of @bayer04fussball. They play Bochum at home next, then Fürth so BVB is safe in second.

author: Sam Spencer
text:
Though it hasn’t been in doubt for weeks, @FCBayern clinched an unprecedented 10th consecutive 1. #Bundesliga title, adding to the clamor that the league is broken. 

On the other hand, #FCBayern has already been knocked out of the @DFB_Pokal and @ChampionsLeague play this year.
